Broader implications? Relevance of this model to our course?\
The results of my experimentation show that multiple factors control the behavior of slime cells. The cells do not merge when the chemical threshold is very high, because they have high resistance to cAMP. Nor do the cells merge when the population is low, or the bias is at a extremely high or low degree level. (However, when population is extremely high, the cells merge almost immediately and form a group).\
The function of the model changes in response to different inputs. Although the main purpose of the model was to form a single, multicellular slime organism, the model was also used to show conditions where the cells would remain distinct. All in all, the model is very adaptive.\
\
